value.value: The reemergence of vaginal carcinoma after a period of remission.
An inflammatory process affecting the salivary duct.
A viral (such as mumps) or bacterial infectious process affecting the salivary gland. The salivary gland becomes enlarged and is often painful.
An acute or chronic infectious process affecting the fallopian tube. Chlamydia trachomatis, Neisseria gonorrhea, Mycoplasma, Staphylococcus, and Streptococcus are the most common causative agents.
A congenital or acquired spinal deformity characterized by lateral curvature of the spine.
An indication or description of an adverse event occurrence.
The toxicity grade value of the adverse event.
A bacterial, fungal or viral infectious process affecting the scrotum.
Painful sensation in the scrotal area.
A laboratory test indicating increased levels of amylase in the serum.
Painful sensation in the face, between the eyes, or upper teeth originating from the sinuses. It is usually caused by sinus infections.

label.value: Localized Digestive System Neuroendocrine Tumor G1

value.value: Digestive system neuroendocrine tumor G1 that is restricted to the site of origin without evidence of metastasis.
Abnormal lightening of skin due to decreased melanin production or deposition. Vitiligo, albinism, and leukoderma are among the disorders that are associated with skin hypopigmentation.
An area of hardness in the skin. Causes include inflammatory process and infiltration of the skin by malignant neoplasms.
Leakage due to breakdown of a small intestinal anastomosis.
An inflammatory process affecting the mucous membrane of the small intestine.
A necrotic process involving the wall of the small intestine.
Blockage of the normal flow of the small intestinal contents.
A rupture in the wall of the small intestine due to traumatic or pathologic processes.
Narrowing of the lumen of small intestine.
An infectious process affecting the small intestine.
A circumscribed inflammatory and necrotic erosive lesion in the mucosa surface of the small intestine.

label.value: Regional Digestive System Neuroendocrine Tumor G1

value.value: Digestive system neuroendocrine tumor G1 that has not spread to other regions.

label.value: Lower Limb Soft Tissue Necrotic Lesion

value.value: A necrotic process affecting the soft tissues of the lower extremity.

label.value: Upper Limb Soft Tissue Necrotic Lesion

value.value: A necrotic process affecting the soft tissues of the upper extremity.
Leakage due to breakdown of a spermatic cord anastomosis.
Bleeding originating from the spermatic cord.
Blockage of the normal flow of the contents of the spermatic cord.
An opening in the wall of the spermatic cord.
Narrowing or stricture of the spermatic cord.

An infectious process affecting the spleen. Predisposing factors include immunosuppression, diabetes mellitus, and sickle cell anemia. Infectious agents include bacteria (e.g., staphylococcus and streptococcus) and fungi.
Narrowing of the lumen of a gastrointestinal stoma.
An infectious process affecting a surgically created opening in the surface of the body.
A painful sensation in the stomach.
Parallel red lines of stretched skin which eventually become whitish. Pregnancy, weight gain and corticosteroids usage are predisposing conditions.
A symptom resulting from laryngeal obstruction. It is characterized by a high pitched breathing sound.
Fibrotic degeneration of the superficial soft tissues.
Thrombosis and inflammation of a superficial vein of the extremities. Symptoms include red discoloration and warmth of the skin and pain along the affected vein.
Bleeding originating from the testis.
A painful sensation in the testis.
A rupture through the testicular tissue.
The development of a blood clot in a catheter.
An infectious process affecting a tooth.

label.value: Recurrent Digestive System Neuroendocrine Tumor G1

value.value: The reemergence of digestive system neuroendocrine tumor G1 after a period of remission.
A painful sensation originating from a tooth.
An abnormal communication between the trachea and another organ or anatomic site.
Bleeding originating from the trachea.
An inflammatory process affecting the wall of the trachea.
An inflammatory process affecting the mucous membrane of the trachea.
Blockage of the lumen of the trachea. Causes include secretions, foreign bodies, and tumors.
